<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="73">Sphaerotrichomes absent. Gonopod aperture large, transversely oval, with small and largely exposed coxites. Telopodites elongate, directed strongly dorsolaterad; seminal groove running along most of telopodite extent on caudal face to terminate distally either on a special branch or tooth (= solenomere), flush on caudal surface, or debauch inside an accessory seminal chamber which normally is supplied with a hairy pulvillus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
